# Restricted Textarea

A simple textarea component with a live character counter and maximum character limit, built using **HTML**, **CSS**, and **JavaScript**.

---

## 📌 Overview

This project implements a textarea that tracks how many characters a user types in real time.

As the user types:

- The character count updates dynamically
- A maximum character limit is enforced
- Once the limit is reached:
  - Additional input is prevented
  - The textarea border turns red as a visual warning

This project is designed to strengthen your understanding of DOM manipulation and user input handling.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Live character count display
- Enforced maximum character limit
- Input restriction when limit is reached
- Visual feedback (red border) on limit
- Simple and responsive UI

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (Vanilla JS)

---

---

## ⚙️ How It Works

- HTML defines the textarea and character counter
- CSS styles the textarea and applies a red border when the limit is reached
- JavaScript:
  - Listens for input events
  - Counts the number of characters entered
  - Updates the counter in real time
  - Prevents additional input when the max limit is reached
  - Adds a visual indicator when the limit is exceeded

